Workflow:
gitri init url dir version

Nomenclature:
repository: a git repository
project: A collection of git repos in a specified layout.  A project is contained in a manifest repo.
revset: A set of revisions of the repositories in a project.  They are named by the branch of the manifest repo in which they are found.

Commands:
init: checkout a new gitri project
reset: reset a subset of repos
revset: create and manipulate revsets
merge: merge repos of other revsets into current one
push: push repo changes to servers

